label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to nucleoplasm during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleoplasm begins later than normal during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to nucleoplasm during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleoplasm is abnormal during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found in the nucleoplasm and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleoplasm during cellular response to hydroxyurea

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to nucleoplasm during cellular response to hydroxyurea

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleoplasm during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleoplasm is decreased during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to nucleoplasm

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to trichostatin A

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to trichostatin A. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of trichostatin A that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to nicotinamide

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to nicotinamide. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of nicotinamide that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased cellular 4'-phosphopantothenate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 4'-phosphopantothenate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: sensitive to stress

value.value: A phenotype in which cells in a population show increased sensitivity to a stress. Typically, a cell population is deemed sensitive to a stress if cells in the population stop growing (and may die) when exposed to the stress at an intensity that allows a population of wild type cells to grow and divide.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. Use a descendant of this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to a stress in culture. If you have assayed the response to the stress at the subcellular or molecular level, consider annotating to a descendant of 'abnormal cellular response to stress' (FYPO:0000162).

label.value: sensitive to UV

value.value: A cell phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to ultraviolet light.

label.value: sensitive to UV during G0

value.value: A cell phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to ultraviolet light during G0 phase.

label.value: lipid droplets present in decreased numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer lipid droplets than normal.

label.value: abnormal double-strand break processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which double-strand break processing is abnormal. Double-strand break processing is the 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang.

label.value: normal protein localization to double-strand break site

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a region of a chromosome at which a DNA double-strand break has occurred is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to medial cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex of a cell is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to medial cortex, with protein distributed in cell cortex near non-growing end, during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex of a cell is decreased, and the protein is instead detected distributed throughout the cell cortex of half of the cell nearer the non-growing end. There may be little or no protein detected at the medial cortex.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to medial cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex is decreased in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the medial cortex and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to medial cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the actomyosin contractile ring is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the actomyosin contractile ring is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the centromere and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the actomyosin contractile ring does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the actomyosin contractile ring begins later than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to nuclear periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nuclear periphery is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased mature tRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell is higher than normal. Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished histone methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone methylation does not occur. All histone methylation may be affected, or methylation of specific sites on specific histones may be abolished.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 does not occur.

label.value: normal centromeric outer repeat transcript level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNAs transcribed from the centromere outer repeat region measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This term encompasses both unprocessed RNA transcribed from the centromere outer repeat region and siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of the primary transcripts. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nuclear periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nuclear periphery is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased cellular dCTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dCTP measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular dATP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dATP measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular dGTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dGTP measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular dTTP level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of dTTP measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased number of Ssb1 foci

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Ssb1 accumulates is greater than normal.

label.value: normal protein localization to centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromosome at long terminal repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein a region in a chromosome that contains one or more long terminal repeats (LTRs) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal chromatin binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is abnormal. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene, and may normally bind DNA, protein, or both in chromatin.

definition.value: This term can mean that the mutated gene product itself binds chromatin differently from wild type, or that a mutation in one gene affects chromatin binding by a second gene product. When using this term, it is therefore recommended to note the specific protein(s) affected.

label.value: decreased chromatin binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene, and may normally bind DNA, protein, or both in chromatin.

label.value: resistance to hydroxyurea

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of hydroxyurea than normal.

label.value: altered mature tRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of mature transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal mature tRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be measured.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased level of nuclear tRNA processing intermediates with 3' extensions

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any tRNA processing intermediates with 3' extensions measured in the nucleus is higher than normal.

label.value: normal mature mitochondrial tRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature mitochondrial transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be measured.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased mature tRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell is lower than normal. Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased mature mitochondrial tRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature mitochondrial transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell is lower than normal. Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mature mitochondrial tRNA absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature mitochondrial transfer RNA (tRNA) measured in a cell is too low to detect. Total tRNA or a specific tRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: normal mitochondrial tRNA 3'-end processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial tRNA 3'-end processing is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). In mitochondrial tRNA 3'-end processing, the 3' end of a mitochondrial pre-tRNA molecule is converted to that of a mature mitochondrial tRNA.

label.value: increased level of mitochondrial polycistronic RNA precursors

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any mitochondrially-encoded polycistronic RNA precursors measured in the cell is higher than normal.

label.value: resistance to nickel

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of nickel ions than normal.

label.value: resistance to zinc

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of zinc ions than normal.
